                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(10)\">\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">\n                                        <placeName>Sussex Hall</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(12)\">\n                                        <date>Feby 17. 1852</date>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>\n                                        <addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">I received with great pleasure your letter<lb/> of\n                                        the <date>25th Novr</date> and can assure you that I\n                                        esteemed<lb/> it an honor to receive a communication from\n                                        one so well known by<lb/> his literary reputation both in\n                                                  <placeName>America</placeName> &amp;\n                                                  <placeName>England</placeName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I can assure you that my business during the<lb/>\n                                        months of <date>December</date> &amp; <date>January</date>\n                                        occupies so much of my time<lb/> that I am precluded from\n                                        attending to any private mat<lb/>ters, and the letter which\n                                        I received from my brother in<lb/>\n                                        <placeName><sic>Cincinatti</sic></placeName> by the mail\n                                        which brought me your favor<lb/> was only answered last\n                                        week. This explanation will I<lb/> hope be considered by you\n                                        satisfactory, and an<lb/> ample apology for not replying to\n                                        you ere this.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I think it better to have to state openly to you\n                                        the<lb/> reason why I cannot undertake to <sic>percure</sic>\n                                        subscribers<lb/> for your Bible, than to lead you to believe\n                                        that I am<lb/> either unwilling or too lazy to attempt to do\n                                        so. You<lb/> are aware that <persName>Dr. Berusch</persName>\n                                        who is in intimate terms<lb/> with me announced some time\n                                        ago his intention<lb/> of publishing a translation of the\n                                        Bible, and when it<lb/> was intended to form a committee for\n                                        the purpose of<lb/> aiding him pecuniarily in the task I\n                                        acted as the<lb/> Honorary Secretary of the same. That plan\n                                        being abandon<lb/>ed &amp; the doctor undertaking the task\n                                        in his own respon-<lb/>sibility I lent him my assistance in\n                                        procuring subscribers<lb/> and the first part of the work\n                                        viz the Pentateuch is already<lb/> in the hands of\n                                                  600<add>?</add> subscribers I need not tell\n                                        you<lb/> that a person on the spot has a great advantage\n                                        over<lb/> one living at a distance. <persName>D.\n                                                  B</persName> has announced his inten</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bz61v33/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
