              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bz61v33/manifest/annotation/p3",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>for another. I must express my surprise that in the<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>United States</placeName> occupied by so many\n                                        Jews you can<lb/> not find supporters enough, for the\n                                        \"Chronicle is<lb/> supported here altho many are very\n                                        dissatisfied<lb/> with it.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I cannot say who was the person who\n                                        corres-<lb/>ponded for your paper under the signature of\n                                                  <persName>O</persName>.<lb/> I have been often\n                                        asked whether I was the<lb/> writer &amp; can assure you\n                                        that I was not.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">To reply to your request that I should write\n                                        a<lb/> monthly letter for your Journal in the state of<lb/>\n                                        Jewish affairs in <placeName>England</placeName>, I will\n                                        undertake<lb/> the task with pleasure if you think I can\n                                        be<lb/> of any service to you. I should wish to remain<lb/>\n                                        incrg—for I do not like as I am holding public<lb/> offices\n                                        to write under my name as I might feel<lb/> my opinions\n                                                  <sic>obacstled</sic> if therefore you wish<lb/> me\n                                        to do as you have requested a letter in reply<lb/> to this\n                                        shall have in return my first letter to<lb/> the occident\n                                        which I will sign <add>משה</add> that being<lb/> my name in\n                                        hebrew.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Should you ever intend paying us a visit\n                                                  <del>in<lb/>this,</del> thinking that a personal\n                                        interview with our<lb/> co-religionists in this city, would\n                                        lend to give a<lb/> larger circulation to your periodical I\n                                        shall be<lb/> most happy to see you &amp; render you every\n                                        assistance<lb/> in my power</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">I am</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(10)\">Dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(11)\">yours Truly</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Morris S. Oppenheim</persName>\n                              </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3bz61v33/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
